<p>In my previous school, an attitude of rote learning towards your exams and sycophancy towards your teacher got you to the top of the education ladder. My new school was different. No one really cared. Instead, they cared about silly things: things  like arts, sports, and power.</p>

<p>Everyone believed, quite paradoxically, that they are THE shit. 
