<p>St. Edmunds didnâ€™t really uphold high standards of moral education, and didnâ€™t really have stricter discipline, nor better scholastic records.</p>

<p>Smoked. Lunch time bullying. Pornographic magazines in their desks. Cars with VIP headlights.</p>

<p>I wanted to gel instraightaway, to mix in, to look and feel like I belonged. I had my breadth -  I was the best wickerkeeper-batsman in my neighbourhood, was well versed with countless mythological tales from my grandpaâ€™s storytellings, and I read my newspaper. I could even even recite a few dohas by Kabir and a poem of Tagore or two.</p>

