This is not about campus politics, nor about love stories. This is not about what sells. This is about the untold that needs to be told.
Just like method actors assimilate the character they are supposed to be playing into their very identities, it also felt like I had been living the book just in order to write it. It is a story I wanted to write than the story I saw. Much like the pensieve reified the memories in Harry Potter, this story reifies certain tendencies. These tendencies are not a universal human characteristic, but something brought about by the way our culture and society are shaping up. So it is important to tell these stories, to make these abstract patterns concrete, give them form, so that we can tackle them better, we can see them, recognize them, and acknowledge them . A novel is the mapping of a writerâ€™s experience onto a waking dream,-->

